---
import RootLayout from '../../layouts/RootLayout.astro';
---

<RootLayout
	title="Own Your Website | Noza LLC"
	description="Stop renting slow websites. Own a performance-first site built to generate leads and scale with modern search."
	lang="en"
	alternateUrl="/es/websites/own-your-website"
>
	<!-- SECTION 1: HERO -->
	<section id="hero" class="hero-section">
		<div class="cosmic-background" aria-label="Animated background design" role="presentation">
			<div class="stars" aria-hidden="true"></div>
			<div class="nebula nebula-1" aria-hidden="true"></div>
			<div class="nebula nebula-2" aria-hidden="true"></div>
			<div class="nebula nebula-3" aria-hidden="true"></div>
		</div>
		<div class="particles" aria-hidden="true"></div>
		
		<div class="hero-content">
			<h1 class="hero-headline">Own Your Website | Performance-First Builds for KY Businesses</h1>
			<p class="hero-subheadline">Stop paying monthly for slow websites that don't deliver results. Own a high-performance site that brings leads to your door.</p>
			<p style="text-align: center; font-size: 0.95rem; color: var(--primary-neon); font-weight: 600; margin: 1.5rem 0 0.75rem 0;">Limited Time • Complimentary</p>
			<div class="hero-buttons">
				<a href="#review" class="cta-primary">GET PERFORMANCE REVIEW</a>
				<a href="/contact" class="cta-secondary">See How It Works</a>
			</div>
			<p style="text-align: center; font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--text-secondary); margin-top: 0.75rem;">$100 Value at No Cost</p>
			<p style="text-align: center; font-size: 0.95rem; color: var(--text-secondary); margin-top: 1rem;">Fast review. Clear recommendations. No pressure.</p>
		</div>
	</section>

	<!-- SECTION 2: HIDDEN PROBLEM -->
	<section id="problem" class="problem-section">
		<div class="problem-container">
			<h2 class="section-title">Why Most Business Websites Underperform</h2>
			
			<div class="problem-content">
				<ul class="problem-bullets">
					<li>Your site shares hosting with hundreds of other businesses—resources get bottlenecked, your pages load slower.</li>
					<li>Patchwork plugins and third-party code slow everything down. Every plugin adds bloat and complexity.</li>
					<li>Monthly subscription fees keep rising, but your site stays the same. You're paying to rent, not build.</li>
					<li>Your site isn't built for how people actually search and browse today. Slow load times mean visitors bounce before they see your message.</li>
				</ul>
				
				<div class="problem-emphasis">
					<p class="emphasis-line">Speed comes from architecture — not patches. <a href="#quick-test" style="color: var(--primary-neon); text-decoration: underline; cursor: pointer;">Test yours with Google's Performance tool</a>—it directly affects rankings.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>

	<!-- SECTION 3: RENT VS OWN COMPARISON -->
	<section id="compare" class="comparison-section">
		<div class="comparison-container">
			<h2 class="section-title">Renting vs Owning Your Website</h2>
			
			<div class="comparison-cards">
				<div class="comparison-card renting-card">
					<h3 class="card-title">Renting (Traditional Platforms)</h3>
					<ul class="comparison-list">
						<li>Monthly fees forever—and they keep going up.</li>
						<li>Templates and plugins pile up, slowing your site down.</li>
						<li>Limited control over how your site looks and functions.</li>
						<li>Performance is capped by the platform's infrastructure.</li>
						<li>You don't own the code or the data underneath.</li>
					</ul>
				</div>
				
				<div class="comparison-card owning-card">
					<h3 class="card-title">Owning (NOZA Build)</h3>
					<ul class="comparison-list">
						<li>One-time build cost. No recurring platform fees.</li>
						<li>Clean, fast foundation built from the ground up.</li>
						<li>You own the site and the code. It's yours.</li>
						<li>Built to scale with AI and modern search.</li>
						<li>Optional retainers only if you want ongoing support.</li>
					</ul>
				</div>
			</div>
			
			<div class="comparison-anchor">
				<p>We don't charge rent for your website to exist.</p>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>

	<!-- SECTION 4: WHY THIS MATTERS NOW (AI ERA) -->
	<section id="ai" class="ai-section">
		<div class="ai-container">
			<h2 class="section-title">The Web Is Changing. Fast Sites Win.</h2>
			
			<div class="ai-bullets">
				<div class="ai-bullet">
					<span class="bullet-number">1</span>
					<p>People bounce fast if your site lags. Even a 1-second delay costs you visitors and leads.</p>
				</div>
				<div class="ai-bullet">
					<span class="bullet-number">2</span>
					<p>AI search favors clear structure and fast pages. Speed and clarity aren't nice-to-haves anymore—they're ranking factors.</p>
				</div>
				<div class="ai-bullet">
					<span class="bullet-number">3</span>
					<p>Heavy platforms get harder to maintain and improve. You're stuck patching instead of progressing.</p>
				</div>
				<div class="ai-bullet">
					<span class="bullet-number">4</span>
					<p>When you own your site, you adapt quickly without being boxed in. You control the future.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
			
			<p style="text-align: center; font-size: 1.05rem; color: var(--text-primary); margin-top: 2.5rem; font-weight: 600;">We build sites that load fast, read clearly, and convert.</p>
		</div>
	</section>

	<!-- SECTION 5: WHAT NOZA OFFERS -->
	<section id="offers" class="offers-section">
		<div class="offers-container">
			<h2 class="section-title">What NOZA Offers</h2>
			
			<div class="offers-cards">
				<div class="offer-card offer-card-a">
					<h3 class="offer-title">One-Time Website Build</h3>
					<ul class="offer-list">
						<li>Performance-first pages that load fast and convert visitors.</li>
						<li>You own your website and the code underneath it.</li>
						<li>Built to generate calls, inquiries, and business results.</li>
					</ul>
				</div>
				
				<div class="offer-card offer-card-b">
					<h3 class="offer-title">Optional Growth Retainers</h3>
					<p style="margin-bottom: 1.5rem; color: var(--text-secondary); font-size: 0.95rem;">For businesses that want ongoing growth support:</p>
					<ul class="offer-list">
						<li>Content updates and new pages</li>
						<li>Landing pages for campaigns</li>
						<li>Social media management</li>
						<li>AI receptionist and follow-up automation</li>
						<li>AI scheduling and appointment booking</li>
						<li>Ongoing SEO and conversion improvements</li>
					</ul>
				</div>
			</div>
			
			<p style="text-align: center; font-size: 1rem; color: var(--text-secondary); margin-top: 2rem; font-weight: 500;">Own your website outright — add services only when they make sense.</p>
		</div>
	</section>

	<!-- SECTION 6: WHO THIS IS FOR / NOT FOR -->
	<section id="fit" class="fit-section">
		<div class="fit-container">
			<h2 class="section-title">Is This the Right Fit?</h2>
			
			<div class="fit-columns">
				<div class="fit-card fit-for">
					<h3 class="fit-title">This Is For You If…</h3>
					<ul class="fit-list">
						<li>Your website is slow or outdated and it's costing you business.</li>
						<li>You want more calls and inquiries from people finding you online.</li>
						<li>You're tired of paying monthly just to keep your site alive.</li>
						<li>You want a long-term foundation you can grow and scale with.</li>
					</ul>
				</div>
				
				<div class="fit-card fit-not-for">
					<h3 class="fit-title">This Is NOT For You If…</h3>
					<ul class="fit-list">
						<li>You only want the absolute cheapest option, no matter the trade-offs.</li>
						<li>You want a quick template with no strategy or customization.</li>
						<li>You prefer relying on lots of plugins and patches to get by.</li>
						<li>You want "set it and forget it"—websites require attention to stay competitive.</li>
					</ul>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>

	<!-- SECTION 7: CONVERSION / REVIEW FORM -->
	<section id="review" class="review-section">
		<div class="review-container">
			<h2 class="section-title">Start With a Complimentary Performance Review</h2>
			
			<p style="text-align: center; color: var(--text-secondary); font-size: 1rem; max-width: 700px; margin: 0 auto 2.5rem; line-height: 1.7;">We'll review your current site and show what's holding it back and improvements you could make today. You'll get clear, practical next steps.</p>
			
			<div class="form-wrapper">
				<!-- Option 1: Submit Form -->
				<form class="review-form" method="POST" action="https://formspree.io/f/myzojzzw">
					<div class="form-group">
						<label for="name">Name *</label>
						<input type="text" id="name" name="name" required placeholder="Your name" aria-required="true" />
					</div>
					
					<div class="form-group">
						<label for="business">Business Name *</label>
						<input type="text" id="business" name="business" required placeholder="Your business name" aria-required="true" />
					</div>
					
					<div class="form-group">
						<label for="website-url">Website URL</label>
						<input type="url" id="website-url" name="website-url" placeholder="https://example.com (or leave blank)" />
					</div>
					
					<div class="form-group">
						<label for="email">Email *</label>
						<input type="email" id="email" name="email" required placeholder="your@email.com" aria-required="true" aria-describedby="email-help" />
						<small id="email-help" style="color: var(--text-secondary); font-size: 0.75rem; margin-top: 0.25rem; display: block;">We'll only use this to send your performance review.</small>
					</div>
					
					<div class="form-group">
						<label for="phone">Phone</label>
						<input type="tel" id="phone" name="phone" placeholder="Your phone number" />
					</div>
					
					<button type="submit" class="cta-primary" aria-label="Submit form to request your complimentary performance review">Request My Review</button>
					
					<div id="form-status" role="status" aria-live="polite" aria-atomic="true" style="margin-top: 1rem; color: var(--primary-neon); font-weight: 600; display: none;">Form submitted successfully! Check your email for your performance review.</div>
					
					<p class="form-trust-note">No spam. No pressure. Just clarity.</p>
				</form>
				
				<p style="text-align: center; font-size: 0.9rem; color: var(--text-secondary); margin-top: 2rem;">Serving Lexington Kentucky & Beyond.</p>
			</div>
			
			<!-- Divider -->
			<div style="text-align: center; position: relative; padding: 0 2rem; margin: 2.5rem 0;">
				<div style="border-top: 1px solid var(--border-glow);"></div>
				<span style="position: absolute; left: 50%; top: -12px; transform: translateX(-50%); background: var(--dark-bg); padding: 0 1rem; color: var(--text-secondary); font-size: 0.85rem;">OR</span>
			</div>
			
			<!-- Option 2: Quick Test -->
			<div id="quick-test" style="text-align: center;">
				<p style="font-size: 0.95rem; color: var(--text-secondary); margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">Quick: Test your site speed first</p>
				
				<div style="display: flex; gap: 0.75rem; max-width: 500px; margin: 0 auto 1.5rem; flex-wrap: wrap; justify-content: center;">
					<input 
						type="url" 
						id="domain-input" 
						placeholder="yourdomain.com"
						style="padding: 0.75rem 1rem; border: 1px solid var(--border-glow); border-radius: 0.5rem; background: rgba(0,212,255,0.05); color: var(--text-primary); font-size: 0.95rem; flex: 1; min-width: 200px;"
					/>
					<button 
						id="pagespeed-btn"
						class="cta-secondary"
						style="padding: 0.75rem 1.5rem; white-space: nowrap;"
					>Test Your Site Speed</button>
				</div>
				<p style="font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--text-secondary);">Opens Google's PageSpeed Insights auditor</p>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>

	<!-- SECTION 7: FAQs -->
	<section id="faqs" class="faqs-section">
		<div class="faqs-container">
			<h2 class="section-title">Common Questions</h2>
			
			<div class="faqs-grid" role="region" aria-labelledby="faqs-heading">
				<div class="faq-item" role="region" aria-labelledby="faq-1">
					<h3 id="faq-1" class="faq-question">Do I really own my website?</h3>
					<p class="faq-answer">Yes. You own the code, the domain, and the site itself. There's no platform lock-in or surprise fees. You can move it anywhere or modify it yourself. This is the fundamental difference between owning and renting.</p>
				</div>
				
				<div class="faq-item" role="region" aria-labelledby="faq-2">
					<h3 id="faq-2" class="faq-question">Why are monthly website fees so common?</h3>
					<p class="faq-answer">Platforms need recurring revenue, so they lock you in. WordPress hosting, Wix, Squarespace, page builders—they all charge monthly because that's their business model. With a built website, you own it outright. One cost, no recurring fees unless you choose growth support.</p>
				</div>
				
				<div class="faq-item" role="region" aria-labelledby="faq-3">
					<h3 id="faq-3" class="faq-question">Is WordPress bad for small businesses?</h3>
					<p class="faq-answer">WordPress itself isn't bad, but it's bloated for most small businesses. It requires hosting, plugins, maintenance, and security updates. A custom-built site is simpler, faster, more secure, and requires less upkeep. Choose the right tool for your needs—not the most popular one.</p>
				</div>
				
				<div class="faq-item" role="region" aria-labelledby="faq-4">
					<h3 id="faq-4" class="faq-question">Can a faster website really get more leads?</h3>
					<p class="faq-answer">Absolutely. Google ranks faster sites higher. People bounce from slow pages. AI search favors fast, clear pages. A 1-second delay costs visitors and conversions. Speed isn't a nice-to-have—it directly affects your bottom line.</p>
				</div>
				
				<div class="faq-item" role="region" aria-labelledby="faq-5">
					<h3 id="faq-5" class="faq-question">Will my website work with AI search?</h3>
					<p class="faq-answer">Yes. AI search engines like ChatGPT, Perplexity, and Claude index well-structured, fast websites. They reward clarity and performance. A built-from-scratch site with clean code ranks better than bloated platform sites in AI search results.</p>
				</div>
				
				<div class="faq-item" role="region" aria-labelledby="faq-6">
					<h3 id="faq-6" class="faq-question">What if I'm tired of paying my web guy every month?</h3>
					<p class="faq-answer">That's exactly the problem we solve. Own your site outright. Pay once for a build, then decide if you want optional growth support. No more surprise invoices or dependency on one person. Control your own web presence.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>
</RootLayout>

